annotationA: Protein 60A; Required for the growth of imaginal tissues and for patterning of the adult wing; Belongs to the TGF-beta family
annotationB: Serine/threonine-protein kinase receptor; Punt (Put) is a transforming growth factor beta type II receptor that functions in both Dpp/BMP and Activin signaling. Pathway specificity in signaling output is determined by which type I receptor (Dpp/BMP or Activin one) is engaged in the complex with Put
